items.title: Hannah Davis
items.caption: The 2015 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue covergirl has taken up the game with boyfriend Derek Jeter hitting the links more since retiring from baseball.

items.title: Kate Upton
items.caption: Upton appeared on the cover of Golf Digest in December 2013 alongside Arnold Palmer. Hopefully, the tips the King gave one of modeling's queens are paying off.

items.title: Kelly Rohrbach
items.caption: Sports Illustrated's swimsuit rookie of the year in 2015 is one of the best golfers on this list. Rohrbach was a member of Georgetown's women's golf team in college.

items.title: Kira Kazantsev
items.caption: Miss America 2015 is an avid player and was a Nike-sponsored golfer at 12. Let's raise awareness about the game among the country's youth, OK, Kira?

items.title: Behati Prinsloo
items.caption: The Victoria Secret model also happens to be married to golf fanatic and rockstar Adam Levine. Here, she practices in the couple's backyard driving range.

items.title: Nina Agdal
items.caption: Another former SI Swimsuit Issue covergirl, Agdal is very keen on improving her game. She told TMZ in January 2015 that she can hit the ball 200 yards. Keep taking lessons, Nina, and that number will continue to go up.

items.title: Jessica Alba
items.caption: The actress is a frequent pro-am participant, teaming up with John Daly at the 2014 Mission Hills World Celebrity Pro-Am.

items.title: Minka Kelly
items.caption: The "Friday Night Lights" star spends plenty of Saturdays and Sundays on the links.

items.title: Catherine Zeta-Jones
items.caption: The actress and husband actor Michael Douglas have long been mainstays on the celebrity golf circuit.
items.credit: Athit Perawongmetha/Getty Images for Mission Hills

items.title: Cameron Diaz
items.caption: There's a great scene in "There's Something About Mary" when Diaz goes to the driving range. She's been known to do the same in real life, too.

items.title: Blair O'Neal
items.caption: The two-time NCAA long drive champ and pro golfer is more of a pro golf model these days.

items.title: Anna Rawson
items.caption: Another pro golfer/model, Rawson played three years (2008-2010) on the LPGA Tour. In 2015, she received her an MBA from Columbia Business School.

items.title: Holly Sonders
items.caption: A former collegiate golfer at Michigan State, Sonders rose to fame on Golf Channel as a host of "Morning Drive." The May 2013 Golf Digest covergirl currently works for Fox Sports.

items.title: Paulina Gretzky
items.caption: The May 2014 Golf Digest covergirl is the fiancee of Dustin Johnson and a quickly improving golfer.

items.title: Ivanka Trump
items.caption: The daughter of The Donald showed off her great swing (wearing heels, no less) at the opening of Trump Golf Links at Ferry Point in 2015.

items.title: Nicole Kidman
items.caption: The longtime actress recently took up golf because she finds it "relaxing." Kidman got tips at the 2014 Mission Hills World Celebrity Pro-Am from fellow Aussie Greg Norman, who gave her a 6 out of 10 for her golf -- for now.

items.title: Heather Locklear
items.caption: While her golf game isn't quite that of former fiance and fellow Melrose Place cast member Jack Wagner, Locklear has maintained her love of the sport. She hosted the 2015 LAPD Memorial Fund Celebrity Charity Golf Tournament.

items.title: Kristen Stewart
items.caption: The "Twilight' star is an an avid golfer who employs an interesting technique on the course: "I just do the best impression of Tiger Woods that I can, and all of a sudden, my swing is dead straight." Hmm. We'll have to try that.

items.title: Eva Longoria
items.caption: The former "Desperate Housewives" actress hosts her own charity golf tournament in Spain.
items.credit: Michael Buckner/Getty Images for The Lopez Foundation

items.title: Tea Leoni
items.caption: The actress is an avid golfer who sports a handicap of around 12. Leoni showed off her skills in a 2014 episode of "Madam Secretary."

items.title: Charlize Theron
items.caption: Theron played a golfer's wife in "The Legend of Bagger Vance," but in real life, she plays golf herself.

items.title: Shakira
items.caption: The pop star's "Hips Don't Lie" on the golf course, either, playing during downtime while on tour.

items.title: Aimee Garcia
items.caption: The "Dexter" and "Vegas" actress hit her first golf shot while caddying for George Lopez at his annual celebrity tournament. She has a handicap of around 25.

items.title: Julia LaCour
items.caption: This photo is a screenshot of a video the model/actress posted of her doing a dance after making a birdie. We like her enthusiasm for the game, but hope she doesn't do that to her opponents in real matches.

items.title: Paige Renee
items.caption: The former San Diego State golfer has become an Instagram star since graduating. The winner of the 2015 Colorado State Match Play, she's probably the best current player on this list.
